cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper addresses the problem of person re-identification using deep learning techniques and convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel multi-resolution network architecture, which involves the use of different levels of features and overlapping stripes. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of different loss functions to combine local and global information, which may be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
